{{Infobox software | name = FET Free Timetabling Software | logo = | screenshot = Fet-software-screenshot-teachers-timetable.png | caption = Screenshot of FET, view of teachers timetable | author = Liviu Lalescu | developer = Liviu Lalescu, Volker Dirr and others | released = 2002 | latest release version = 5.37.2 | latest release date = {{start date and age|2018|8|15}} | latest preview version = | latest preview date = | programming language = [[C++]]<ref>https://lalescu.ro/liviu/fet/download.html</ref> | operating system = [[Windows 7]] and later, [[Mac OS X]], [[GNU/Linux]] | platform = [[Qt (software)|Qt]] | size = 11–16 MB | language = | status = | genre = | license = [[GNU AGPL]] v3 | website = {{URL|https://lalescu.ro/liviu/fet/}} }}
'''FET''' is a [[free and open-source]] [[School timetable|time tabling app]] for automatically scheduling the timetable of a school, high-school or university. FET is written in [[C++]] using the [[Qt (software)|Qt]] [[cross-platform]] [[application framework]]. Initially, FET stood for "Free Evolutionary Timetabling"; as it is no longer evolutionary, the E in the middle can stand for anything the user prefers.<ref>''[http://lalescu.ro/liviu/fet/forum/index.php?topic=1085.msg6259#msg6259]''Posting by Liviu Lalescu, main developer</ref>
Custom made versions of FET are available for Moroccan, Algerian and US high-schools.<ref>''[http://lalescu.ro/liviu/fet/custom.html]''List of custom made versions of FET</ref>
==FET Features==
* Localized to many languages;<ref>''[http://lalescu.ro/liviu/fet/features.html]''Official feature list with available languages</ref> * Fully automatic generation algorithm, allowing also semi-automatic or manual allocation; * Platform independent implementation; * Flexible modular XML format for the input file; * Import/export from CSV format; * The resulted timetables are exported into HTML, XML and CSV formats;
