{{one source|date=February 2017}}
'''MEMS sensor generations''' represent the progress made in micro [[sensor]] technology and can be categorized as follows:

;1st Generation :[[Microelectromechanical systems|MEMS]] sensor element mostly based on a [[silicon]] structure, sometimes combined with [[analog circuit|analog]] amplification on a [[integrated circuit|micro chip]].<ref>S.C.Terry,J.H.Jerman and J.B.Angell:A Gas Chromatographic Air Analyzer Fabricated on a Silicon Wafer,IEEE Trans.Electron Devices,ED-26,12(1979)1880-1886.</ref>

;2nd Generation:MEMS sensor element combined with analog amplification and [[analog-to-digital converter]] on one micro chip.

;3rd Generation :Fusion of the sensor element with analog amplification, analog-to-digital converter and [[Digital data|digital]] intelligence for linearization and temperature compensation on the same micro chip.

;4th Generation :Memory cells for calibration- and temperature compensation data are added to the elements of the 3rd MEMS sensor generation.

