{{Infobox person | name = Sébastienne Guyot | birth_date = 26 April 1896 | birth_place = [[Pont-l'Abbé]], [[Finistère]], [[France]] | death_date = {{death date and age|1941|8|21|1896|4|26|df=yes}}<ref name="FrenchAthletics">{{cite web|last = Dupuy|first = Gérard|url = http://cdm.athle.com/upload/ssites/001059/jeux%20olympiques/femmesal200517.pdf|title = Les Jeux Olympiques|date = 20 May 2017|publisher = [[French Athletics Federation]]|access-date = 12 August 2017}}</ref> | death_place = [[Paris]], [[Île-de-France]], [[France]] | nationality = [[France|French]] | occupation = [[Engineer]], [[Pilot (aeronautics)|Pilot]] | image = Sébastienne Guyot.jpg }}
'''Sébastienne Guyot''' (26 April 1896 &ndash; 21 August 1941) was a French [[engineer]] who specialized in [[Aerodynamics|aerodynamic]] flying. She was born in [[Pont-l'Abbé|Pont l'Abbé]] in the [[Finistère]].
A teacher, Guyot resigned in 1917 to prepare for the competition of the Ecole Centrale of the Paris [[Lycée Jules-Ferry (Paris)|Lycée Jules-Ferry]] when she learned that the school would accepts girls into its ranks. She graduated in 1921 from the first class of [[École Centrale Paris|Central School of Paris]] to accept women. She ranked 45th of 243 graduates (425 students were received in the contest).<ref>{{Cite web|title=biographie/Sébastienne Guyot|url=http://centrale-histoire.centraliens.net/pdfs/biographies/SebastienneGUYOT.pdf|accessdate=8 March 2015}}</ref>
Also a [[Athlete|top athlete]], she participated in the [[1928 Summer Olympics|1928 Summer Olympics in Amsterdam]] in the [[800 metres|800 meters]]. She was also [[:fr:Championnats de France de cross-country|French Cross Country Champion]] in 1928. Arrested by the Germans in 1940, she died in 1941 in [[Paris]]
== Legacy == Guyot was awarded the medal of the resistance posthumously. She is the only woman whose name is on the war memorial of the Ecole Centrale. Since 2010, a scholarship in her name is given annually to five young Ecole Centrale students to fully fund their studies at the School. In 2015, her name was given to one of the eight streets in the new university area of Moulon in Gif-sur-Yvette, an area that will accommodate [[CentraleSupélec]] in 2017, following the merger and Centrale Paris and [[Supélec]].<ref>{{Citation|language=fr|title=Conseil municipal du 10 février 2015.|periodical=Bulletin municipal de Gif-sur-Yvette|date =March 2015}}</ref>
